Program: Outlook
Title: 23/04/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00qqq6m
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 24 Apr 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Matthew Bannister hears from Oh Kil-nam, the South Korean man who has not seen his wife and children since he defected from North Korea 20 years ago. Also in the programme, the British advertising executive who spent years in Malaysia learning from a Kung Fu Grandmaster. And Rana Jawad, the BBC journalist who risked her life to write an undercover blog during the Libyan revolution. Show less